comment_data.body:
I have the same issue, i found one workaround so far but it really sucks:
1. backup your project directory
2. Using the IDE and Flutter plugin, create a new flutter project on your current project directory, match as many settings as you can (path and domain are really it).  Don't forget to re-add your arguments when the new project starts up, e.g. --no-sound-null-safety
3. don't restart the IDE or you will see the error again. :)

I think best way is to avoid the new Android Studio patch.
